The root cause was simple: we changed the shell script from `ros2 run` to `ros2 launch`.
[/THINK]
[2026-06-11T10:08:39.250Z] [THINK]
 `ros2 run` directly connects the process's stdin to the terminal, so `getchar()` works. But
[/THINK]
[2026-06-11T10:08:39.681Z] [THINK]
 `ros2 launch` by default does NOT forward stdin — it runs the node with stdin disconnected
[/THINK]
[2026-06-11T10:08:40.100Z] [THINK]
, so `getchar()` returns EOF immediately every time.

The fix is adding `emulate_tty=True` to the `Node(...)` definition in the
[/THINK]
[2026-06-11T10:08:40.540Z] [THINK]
 launch file, which tells ROS2 launch to forward stdin properly.

Now, since the installed symlink points
[/THINK]
[2026-06-11T10:08:40.953Z] [THINK]
 to the source file, the change should take effect without another build if using the installed
[/THINK]
[2026-06-11T10:08:41.399Z] [THINK]
 launch file. But the build is always safe.

